{{World's Strongest Man Contestbox |Name =2002 World's Strongest Man |Logo =WSMLogo.jpg |Host city = {{flagicon|MYS}} [[Kuala Lampur]], [[Malaysia]] |Nations participating =18 |Athletes participating =30 |Winner = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Mariusz Pudzianowski]] |previous = [[2001 World's Strongest Man|Victoria Falls 2001]] |next = [[2003 World's Strongest Man|Victoria Falls 2003]] }}
The '''2002 World's Strongest Man''' was the 25th edition of the international [[World's Strongest Man]] competition, and was won by [[Mariusz Pudzianowski]] from [[Poland]]. The contest was held in [[Kuala Lampur]], [[Malaysia]].<ref name=" theworldsstrongestman.com ">{{cite web |url= http://www.theworldsstrongestman.com/2002_results.php |title= theworldsstrongestman.com |accessdate=2010-01-16| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100104031830/http://theworldsstrongestman.com/2002_results.php| archivedate= 4 January 2010 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= yes}}</ref>
