{{Distinguish|All Seasons Arena (Minot)}}
'''All Seasons Arena''' is a two-rink facility built in 1973 and located in [[Mankato, Minnesota]], United States. It is the former home of the [[Minnesota State Mavericks women's ice hockey]].

The arena is also used for practices by the [[Minnesota State Mavericks men's ice hockey]] team. It was used for men's intercollegiate games until 1995, when they moved to the newly opened [[Verizon Center (Mankato, Minnesota)|Verizon Center]].

